  <p>
    Installing or replacing a septic system is the biggest undertaking in owning one, and unlike a
    routine pump-out, its budget genuinely can't be read off a chart. That's not vagueness — it's
    because the system is engineered for a specific piece of ground, and the ground varies enormously
    across the Upper Cumberland, from plateau rock to river-valley bottomland. Understanding the
    factors that shape the budget helps you plan realistically and ask good questions before ground
    breaks.
  </p>

  {/* Intended asset: /images/resources/new-septic-installation-cost-factors-hero.webp — see public/images/resources/README.md */}
